h lacks clear id/values compared to the jsp-api source. It might be that the active class in jsp-api only has one call, which the existing servlet-api test covers. If `Tag.class.isAssignableFrom(TagSupport.class)` evaluates as true, I'll need to consider the implications. I should avoid direct reflection in tests to maintain simplicity and avoid introducing unnecessary complexity.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class selection methods**\\n\\nI’m thinking about adding a helper method `private Class<?> typeOf(Object value)` to return the class type of an object, which could help avoid using constants. I could call `TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, parent.getClass())` and consider passing `child.getParent().getClass()`. Using a system property to determine the class at runtime could be another approach, but I’m balancing that with ensuring I don’t fold `Object.getClass`. \\n\\nTo prevent build-time constants, I'm exploring ways to ensure tests stay deterministic, looking into using `System.nanoTime()`. But there's a risk that it could yield negative values, which complicates things.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_r5KlyTznKdxJJ4IDOg0UmizI|fc_05ffc76838a427720169f9d24dee8881a29172a083b0660a91", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/src/test/java/javax_servlet/jsp_api/TagSupportTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    void findAncestorWithClassUsesClassicTagHierarchy() {\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\n        TagSupport grandparent = new TagSupport();\n        child.setParent(parent);\n        parent.setParent(grandparent);\n\n        Tag ancestor = TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, TagSupport.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\n    }\n", "newText": "    void findAncestorWithClassUsesClassicTagHierarchy() {\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\n        TagSupport grandparent = new TagSupport();\n        child.setParent(parent);\n        parent.setParent(grandparent);\n        Class<?> ancestorType = System.nanoTime() == Long.MIN_VALUE ? Tag.class : parent.getClass();\n\n        Tag ancestor = TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, ancestorType);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\n        assertThat(TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, Tag.class)).isSameAs(parent);\n    }\n"}, {"oldText": "    void findAncestorWithClassAcceptsTagInterface() {\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\n        child.setParent(parent);\n\n        Tag ancestor = TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, IterationTag.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\n    }\n", "newText": "    void findAncestorWithClassAcceptsTagInterface() {\n        TagSupport child = new TagSupport();\n        TagSupport parent = new TagSupport();\n        child.setParent(parent);\n\n        Tag ancestor = TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, IterationTag.class);\n\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(parent);\n        assertThat(TagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, Object.class)).isNull();\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 456, "output": 1265, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33977, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777979969654, "responseId": "resp_05ffc76838a427720169f9d2421db481a286e7fff27fe04b85"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_r5KlyTznKdxJJ4IDOg0UmizI|fc_05ffc76838a427720169f9d24dee8881a29172a083b0660a91", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/src/test/java/javax_servlet/jsp_api/TagSupportTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n 24         TagSupport parent = new TagS